这只是个例
But that's a mere detail.

745
01:30:28,381 --> 01:30:30,475
每年无数的人死去
Millions of people die every year

746
01:30:30,634 --> 01:30:34,764
因为那个被称作神父的人渣说不能带套
cos the scumbag they call the Pope says you can't use a condom when having sex.

747
01:30:34,930 --> 01:30:37,934
从历史上看  这是个例
It's only a mere detail, historically speaking,

748
01:30:38,099 --> 01:30:41,353
但对我不是  对我不是啊
but not to me. Not to me.

749
01:30:57,744 --> 01:31:00,418
- 爱丽丝 - 阿拉巴马
Elise. - Alabama.

750
01:31:01,039 --> 01:31:03,292
- 阿拉巴马 - 嗯？
Alabama. - Yes?

751
01:31:04,084 --> 01:31:09,386
如果我愿意相信梅布尔是天上的一颗星星
If I want to believe that Maybelle is a star up in the sky,

752
01:31:09,547 --> 01:31:11,174
我会相信的
I will.

753
01:31:12,175 --> 01:31:16,430
如果我愿意相信她是一只鸟  在窗台上栖息
If I want to believe she's a bird that perches on our window sill,

754
01:31:16,596 --> 01:31:18,690
或者是只蝴蝶  停在我肩膀
or a butterfly that sits on my shoulder

755
01:31:18,848 --> 01:31:23,319
-或者流血的青蛙 - 亲爱的  梅布尔死了
or a bloody frog that... - Maybelle is dead, sweetheart.

756
01:31:23,478 --> 01:31:26,652
她死了  没有了  不在了
She's dead, she's gone! She's not here anymore.

757
01:31:26,815 --> 01:31:28,943
但我们还在这里  我还在这里
But we are still here. I'm still here.

758
01:31:29,109 --> 01:31:32,093
- 我们还得过下去 - 迪迪埃  我已经死心了
We have to carry on together. - I've covered up your name, Didier.

759
01:31:41,830 --> 01:31:44,800
你是个懦夫  彻底的懦夫
You're a coward. You're nothing but a coward.

760
01:31:44,958 --> 01:31:46,926
懦夫
A coward!

761
01:31:48,962 --> 01:31:52,637
梅布尔不会想到会是这样  你为什么这样？
Maybelle wouldn't have wanted that. Why did you do it? Why?

762
01:32:01,057 --> 01:32:02,809
我知道
I knew.

763
01:32:03,226 --> 01:32:06,355
事实上  我一直知道
In fact, I've always known.

764
01:32:07,022 --> 01:32:08,820
这些想象对我来说很好
That it was too wonderful to be true.

765
01:32:08,982 --> 01:32:14,239
但它不能持久  生活不是那样  也并不慷慨
That it couldn't last. That life isn't like that, life isn't generous.

766
01:32:16,031 --> 01:32:20,502
你不能爱任何人  也不能被任何人爱
You mustn't love someone, you mustn't become attached to someone,

767
01:32:20,660 --> 01:32:22,037
生活嫉妒你这些
life begrudges you that.

768
01:32:22,203 --> 01:32:28,006
它夺走你的一切  嘲笑你  背叛你
It takes everything away from you and laughs in your face. It betrays you.

769
01:32:28,168 --> 01:32:32,924
- 亲爱的  别这样 - 别那样叫我  迪迪埃
Sweetheart, don't... - Don't call me that, Didier.

770
01:32:33,089 --> 01:32:35,808
我不再是你的亲爱的
I'm not your sweetheart anymore!

771
01:32:35,967 --> 01:32:37,469
都结束了
It's over!

772
01:33:11,169 --> 01:33:12,671
你还好吗  伙计？
Are you alright, pal?

773
01:33:13,880 --> 01:33:15,382
不好…不过…
No... but...

774
01:33:16,174 --> 01:33:17,266
谢谢
Thanks.

775
01:33:19,469 --> 01:33:23,064
- 我们打算做什么 - 演奏
What are we going to do? - Play.

776
01:33:25,058 --> 01:33:26,480
爱丽丝在哪
Where's Elise?

777
01:34:18,570 --> 01:34:23,497
爸爸  能再说一遍星星吗
Daddy, can you tell me about the stars again?

778
01:34:24,033 --> 01:34:25,376
说些什么？
What about them?

779
01:34:26,786 --> 01:34:30,131
说说它们如何消失
About how they've gone out.

780
01:34:35,753 --> 01:34:37,221
消失？
Gone out?

781
01:34:37,630 --> 01:34:40,133
你以前说过的
You told me before.

782
01:34:42,093 --> 01:34:48,396
对  像这样的小星星
Right. A little star like this one is, in fact a...?

783
01:34:48,558 --> 01:34:51,812
- 太阳 - 太阳  对  梅布尔
A sun. - A sun. Yes, well done, Maybelle.

784
01:34:56,357 --> 01:34:59,406
太阳离我们非常非常遥远
It's a sun that is a very, very long way away.

785
01:34:59,569 --> 01:35:05,372
它的光线很长时间跨越很远很远
And its light has to travel a long way for a long time

786
01:35:05,533 --> 01:35:08,286
才能被我们看到
to reach your eyes.

787
01:35:08,453 --> 01:35:16,508
所以有时  星星已经消失了
So sometimes it's possible that the little star has already gone out

788
01:35:16,669 --> 01:35:21,266
但它们还能被我们看到
before the light reaches your eyes.

789
01:35:21,799 --> 01:35:28,102
所以你只是看到了不复存在的东西
So you see something that is no longer there.

790
01:35:29,057 --> 01:35:33,528
但没有关系  因为星星的光线
But that doesn't matter, because the light from a little star like that

791
01:35:33,686 --> 01:35:37,156
在空间中旅行  被你看到
carries on travelling, past your eyes.

792
01:35:37,315 --> 01:35:39,443
甚至更远  更远
Further and further.

793
01:35:39,609 --> 01:35:42,738
所以星星会一直存在
So that little star will exist forever.

794
01:35:42,904 --> 01:35:45,999
永远  永远
Forever and ever and ever.

795
01:38:05,296 --> 01:38:06,923
爱丽丝
Elise!

796
01:38:22,647 --> 01:38:23,899
天啊
Goddammit!

797
01:38:30,196 --> 01:38:31,413
女士
Madam.

798
01:38:31,572 --> 01:38:34,075
女士  你能听见吗？
Madam. Can you hear me?

799
01:38:41,749 --> 01:38:43,672
